---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SchemaMarkup from "../../components/SchemaMarkup.astro";
import Icon from "../../components/Icon.astro";

// Make this page dynamic via SSR
export const prerender = false;

const publishDate = new Date("November 30 2026");
const author = "The Valley Clean Team";
const readTime = "5 min read";

const isPublished = new Date().getTime() >= publishDate.getTime();

---

<BaseLayout
  title="Post-Thanksgiving Kitchen Mess: Reset Guide"
  description={isPublished ? "Survived Thanksgiving? Now tackle the mess. Our post-Thanksgiving kitchen reset guide helps Alabama and Tennessee homeowners clean up fast after the holiday feast." : "Coming Soon: Surviving the Post-Thanksgiving Mess: Kitchen Reset"}
  noindex={!isPublished}
  ogImage="https://storage.googleapis.com/msgsndr/iKQIBhpKVL2XVPgU7HMd/media/6920802945dc047d65b4ec5d.png"
>
  <SchemaMarkup
    type="article"
    title="Surviving the Post-Thanksgiving Mess: Kitchen Reset"
    description="Overwhelmed by Thanksgiving aftermath? Follow our step-by-step kitchen reset guide to quickly survive and clean up the post-holiday cooking mess."
    publishDate="November 30 2026"
    author={author}
  />
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-gray-800 to-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-[#FFA985]/20 text-[#FFA985] rounded-full text-sm font-medium mb-6">
          Pain Point
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          Surviving the Post-Thanksgiving Mess: Kitchen Reset
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          {isPublished ? "Expert Cleaning Guide" : "Coming November 30 2026."}
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-4 text-gray-400 mb-8">
          <span>November 30 2026</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>{readTime}</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>By {author}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content Toggle based on Published Date -->
  {isPublished ? (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <!-- TODO: REPLACE THIS SECTION WITH YOUR ACTUAL BLOG CONTENT -->
          <h2>How Do You Survive the Post-Thanksgiving Kitchen Mess?</h2>
<p><strong>Surviving the post-Thanksgiving kitchen mess starts with a systematic approach to cleaning up. Begin by tackling the biggest offenders first, like dishes and spills, then move on to surfaces and floors. For those in The Shoals & Surrounding Areas, The Valley Clean Team offers veteran-owned precision to get your kitchen back in pristine condition, guaranteed.</strong></p>

<h3>The Immediate Aftermath: Where to Start</h3>
<p>Thanksgiving is a time for joy and family, but it often leaves behind a kitchen that looks like a battlefield. Start by clearing the clutter. Remove leftovers from the table and store them properly. Next, focus on the dirty dishes, a notorious post-feast headache.</p>
<p>Here’s a streamlined approach to tackle the mess:</p>
<ul>
  <li>**Prioritize:** Start with items that need immediate attention, like soaking pots and pans.</li>
  <li>**Organize:** Sort dishes by type—plates, glasses, cutlery—to streamline washing.</li>
  <li>**Delegate:** If possible, assign tasks to family members, making the process quicker and more efficient.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Restoring Order: Cleaning Surfaces and Appliances</h4>
<p>With dishes out of the way, turn your attention to countertops and appliances. Thanksgiving can leave a trail of crumbs, spills, and unexpected stains.</p>
<p>**Step-by-Step Surface Cleaning:**</p>
<ul>
  <li>**Wipe Down:** Use a gentle cleanser to tackle countertops, focusing on high-traffic areas.</li>
  <li>**Appliances:** Clean the exterior of your stove, oven, and fridge, paying special attention to handles and knobs.</li>
  <li>**Check Cabinets:** Spot clean any spills or splatters on cabinet doors.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Floors: The Final Frontier</h3>
<p>Once surfaces are sparkling, your last challenge is the floor. Thanksgiving dinner often means crumbs and spills underfoot.</p>
<p>**Efficient Floor Cleaning Tips:**</p>
<ul>
  <li>**Sweep First:** Remove crumbs and debris with a broom or vacuum.</li>
  <li>**Mop Thoroughly:** Use a mild floor cleaner suitable for your floor type.</li>
  <li>**Spot Treat:** Don’t forget to address any sticky spots or stains.</li>
</ul>

<h4>The Valley Clean Team: Your Post-Thanksgiving Rescue</h4>
<p>If the post-Thanksgiving mess feels overwhelming, or you simply want to reclaim your time, The Valley Clean Team is here to help. Serving The Shoals & Surrounding Areas, our veteran-owned and operated team specializes in restoring your home to its pristine state.</p>
<p>**What We Offer:**</p>
<ul>
  <li>**Military-Precision Cleaning:** Our specialists follow exact SOPs to guarantee satisfaction.</li>
  <li>**Transparent Pricing:** We offer upfront quotes, starting at $125, with no hidden fees.</li>
  <li>**Community Focus:** As a local business, we understand the needs of our community and are dedicated to providing superior service.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Reclaim Your Time: Book Your Guaranteed Clean Today</h3>
<p>Don't let the post-Thanksgiving mess linger. Reclaim your time and peace of mind by scheduling a professional clean with The Valley Clean Team. Our vetted specialists ensure a thorough clean, every time, guaranteed. Book today and experience the premium care your home deserves.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  ) : (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white border-t border-gray-100 shadow-inner">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-center">
          <Icon name="clock" class="w-16 h-16 text-[#FFA985] mx-auto mb-6" />
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 mt-0">Article Coming Soon!</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 m-0">This article is locked and scheduled to automatically publish on <br/><strong class="text-gray-800 text-xl">November 30 2026</strong>.<br/>Check back then!</p>
          <div class="mt-12">
            <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-lg font-semibold text-white bg-[#FFA985] rounded-full hover:bg-[#ff9a70] transition shadow-md no-underline">
              Back to Blog
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  )}
</BaseLayout>
